{{Infobox Tibetan Buddhist monastery |name = Karma Kagyud Buddhist Centre |image = Karma_Kagyud_Buddhist_Centre_Logo.jpg |image size = |alt = |caption = Karma Kagyud Buddhist Centre |t= |w= |to = |ipa= |z= 新加坡噶玛迦如佛教中心 |thdl= |e= |tc= |s= |p= |pushpin_map = |latd = |longd= |iso_region = |map_caption = |mapsize = |location_country = Singapore |location = [[Geylang]], [[Singapore]] |founded_by = [[Kunzig Shamar Rinpoche]], [[David Chee Kim Swee]] |date_founded = 1979 |date_renovated = |sect = [[Kagyud]] |dedicated_to = [[Trinley Thaye Dorje]] |head_lama = [[Shangpa Rinpoche]] |no._of_monks = |architecture = |footnotes = }} {{Tibetan Buddhism}}
'''Karma Kagyud Buddhist Centre''' ({{zh|s=噶玛迦如佛教中心}}) is one of the several [[Tibetan Buddhism]] [[Vajrayana]] centers in [[Singapore]], {{As of|2015|lc=y}} operating from temporary premises while the permanent building is undergoing reconstruction. The temporary and permanent premises are both in [[Geylang]].
==History==
'''Karma Kagyud Buddhist Centre''' was first initiated in 1979,<ref name="newcenter">{{cite web|title=ABOUT KARMA KAGYUD BUDDHIST CENTRE|url=http://www.buddha.sg/htm/up2005/sep05a.htm|website=Singapore DharmaNet Homepage|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> and after a visit by the [[16th Gyalwa Karmapa]] on 27 December 1980, the centre was officially founded on 17 April 1981 following a visit by [[Kunzig Shamar Rinpoche]] in Singapore.<ref>{{cite web | title = Karma Kagyud Buddhist Centre Singapore | publisher = Facebook | url = https://www.facebook.com/pages/Karma-Kagyud-Buddhist-Centre-Singapore/112601275435639?sk=info | accessdate = 2014-09-10}}</ref> The centre subscribes with the [[Kagyud]] lineage<ref>{{cite web|title=Karma Choying Ling|url=http://www.zoominfo.com/p/Karma-Ling/1155598173|publisher=Zoom Information, Inc|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> of [[Tibetan Buddhism]]<ref>{{cite journal|title=2006 April Activities|journal=For You Information|issue=204|accessdate=9 September 2014}}</ref> and advocates [[Trinley Thaye Dorje]] as the 17th Karmapa<ref>{{cite web|title=Karmapa and Karma Kagyu Tradition|url=http://www.karma-kagyu.org|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> in the ongoing [[Karmapa Controversy]].<ref>{{cite web|title=ABOUT KARMAPA|url=http://www.karmapasingapore2014.com/about-the-event/about-karmapa/|website=The Time is Ripe|publisher=Karma Kagyud Buddhist Centre|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref>
