'''Siva Senai''' is a political group in [[Sri Lanka]] formed to protect the interests of [[Sri Lankan Tamils|Sri Lankan Tamil]] [[Hindus]] formed in October 2016<ref>[http://www.newindianexpress.com/world/2016/oct/12/siva-senai-formed-in-sri-lanka-to-enable-hindus-to-face-threats-from-other-religions-1527283.html 'Siva Senai' formed in Sri Lanka to enable hindus to face threats from other religions] New Indian Express - October 12, 2016</ref>. Maravanpulavu Sachchithananthan, a former [[United Nations]] official is the founder of the group, which has received encouragement from the Indian political party [[Shiv Sena]]<ref>[https://swarajyamag.com/insta/siva-senai-a-hindu-army-in-sri-lanka-to-counter-threats-from-other-religious-groups To Counter Conversions, Sri Lanka’s Hindus Form Siva Senai] Swarajya - October 13, 2016</ref><ref>[http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=153748 Siva Senai in Sri Lanka gets Shiv Sena support] Island - October 14, 2016</ref> Siva Senai spearheaded an initiative in December 2017 to allow Sri Lankan pilgrims to visit [[Chidambaram]] in [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]].<ref>[https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/sri-lankan-tamil-pilgrims-can-travel-to-chidambaram-on-ferry/story-TyJPMgCHEalRFGEwusbVvN.html Sri Lankan Tamil pilgrims can travel to Chidambaram on ferry] Hindustan Times - December 22, 2017</ref>
